<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">For more on the facts about global warming and its causes, see the <a href="http://www.ucsusa.org/global_warming" target="_blank">Union of Concerned Scientists' Global Warming program</a> on its Web site.<p>
For a left commentary on the latest findings of the IPCC, see <a href="http://www.monthlyreview.org/mrzine/cf170207.html" target="_blank">"Is the New UN Global Warming Report Too Conservative?"</a> by Brett Clark and John Bellamy Foster. Lance Newman's <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/40/globalwarming.shtml" target="_blank">"Year of Unnatural Disasters"</a> in a recent <i>International Socialist Review </i>provides another perspective on the issue.<p>
Jeffrey St. Clair's writing on environmental issues and politics appears regularly on the <a href="http://www.counterpunch.org" target="_blank">CounterPunch</a> Web site.<p>
Among his many books are <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBeen-Brown-Long-Looked-Green%2Fdp%2F1567512585%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1180295178%26sr%3D8-12&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Been Brown So Long It Looked Like Green to Me: The Politics of Nature</a></i>, <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPocket-Guide-Environmental-Bad-Guys%2Fdp%2F1560251530%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1180295178%26sr%3D8-13&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">A Pocket Guide to Environmental Bad Guys</a> </i>(with James Ridgeway) and <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGrand-Theft-Pentagon-Corruption-Profiteering%2Fdp%2F1567513360%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1180295178%26sr%3D8-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Grand Theft Pentagon: Tales of Corruption and Profiteering in the War On Terror</a></i>.
</td></tr></table>
